## ✅ CORRECT: Explicit Search Pattern

**MUST use this exact pattern for search conditions:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Only initial load triggers API call
useEffect(() => {
  fetchData(); // Initial load only
}, []);

// ✅ CORRECT: Explicit search handler
const handleSearch = () => {
  setCurrentPage(1); // Reset to first page
  fetchData(); // API call only when user clicks search or presses Enter
};

// ✅ CORRECT: Input field with Enter key support
<input
  type="text"
  value={searchKeyword}
  onChange={(e) => setSearchKeyword(e.target.value)} // State only, no API call
  onKeyPress={(e) => {
    if (e.key === "Enter") {
      handleSearch(); // Explicit API call
    }
  }}
/>

// ✅ CORRECT: Search button
<button onClick={handleSearch}>🔍 조회</button>
```

**Key Requirements:**

- ✅ **Initial Load**: API called once on page load
- ✅ **Explicit Search**: API called only when:
  - User clicks "조회" button
  - User presses Enter key in search input
- ✅ **Input Changes**: State updates only, NO API calls
- ✅ **Table Filters**: Server-side filtering with Debounce (800ms)

