### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Server-Side Filtering with Debounce

**MUST ALWAYS use Debounce (800ms) for table filters when implementing server-side filtering:**

**Why Debounce is Required:**

- **Performance**: Prevents API calls on every keystroke
- **User Experience**: Provides real-time feel without excessive server load
- **Balance**: 800ms balances responsiveness and performance

**Implementation Pattern:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Filters with Debounce 800ms
const [filters, setFilters] = useState({
  userId: "",
  userNm: "",
  emailAdres: "",
  sbscrbDe: "",
  mberSttus: "",
});

// Use ref to hold latest filter values
const filtersRef = useRef(filters);
useEffect(() => {
  filtersRef.current = filters;
}, [filters]);

// Fetch function uses ref, not state directly
const fetchMembers = useCallback(async () => {
  const currentFilters = filtersRef.current; // Use ref
  const params = {
    filterUserId: currentFilters.userId || undefined,
    filterUserNm: currentFilters.userNm || undefined,
    // ... other filters
  };
  // ... API call
}, [currentPage, pageSize]); // ⚠️ filters NOT in dependencies

// Create ref for fetchMembers
const fetchMembersRef = useRef(fetchMembers);
useEffect(() => {
  fetchMembersRef.current = fetchMembers;
}, [fetchMembers]);

// Debounce useEffect (filters in dependencies, but fetchMembers NOT in dependencies)
useEffect(() => {
  if (isInitialLoad) return;

  const timer = setTimeout(() => {
    setCurrentPage(1);
    fetchMembersRef.current(); // Use ref to call latest function
  }, 800);

  return () => clearTimeout(timer);
}, [
  filters.userId,
  filters.userNm,
  filters.emailAdres,
  filters.sbscrbDe,
  filters.mberSttus,
  isInitialLoad,
]);
```

**Key Requirements:**

- ✅ **filtersRef**: Holds latest filter values without causing function recreation
- ✅ **fetchMembersRef**: Holds latest fetch function for use in debounce
- ✅ **Debounce 800ms**: Filters trigger API after 800ms of inactivity
- ✅ **Page Reset**: Filters reset to page 1
- ✅ **No fetchMembers in debounce dependencies**: Prevents circular dependency issues

**Common Mistakes:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG: search conditions in fetchMembers dependencies
const fetchMembers = useCallback(async () => {
  const params = {
    searchKeyword: searchKeyword, // Direct state access
  };
}, [currentPage, pageSize, searchKeyword]); // ❌ searchKeyword causes function recreation

// ✅ CORRECT: Use refs
const fetchMembers = useCallback(async () => {
  const params = {
    searchKeyword: searchKeywordRef.current, // Use ref
  };
}, [currentPage, pageSize]); // ✅ No search conditions in dependencies

// Note: NO debounce effect for filters - all filtering is server-side only via API parameters
// NO table filter UI (filter toggle button, filter row) - NOT used in this project
```

