**Why ref gate:** If `isInitialLoad` is in the dependency array, when it flips to false (after first fetch), this effect runs and schedules an 800ms timer that calls `setCurrentPage(1)` and fetch. When returning from detail to list with `?page=2`, that timer overwrites the preserved page to 1. Using `initialLoadDoneRef` and removing `isInitialLoad` from deps prevents the timer from running on mount/return-from-detail; it runs only when filter values actually change.

